When setting up a computer, don't forget to edit the "Sharing" tabs!
Also remove the default folder.
After syncthing first finishes, shut down syncthing then do:
mv ~/tmp72112 ~/public_html/
mv ~/consulting ~/prof/
rm -rf ~/Sync
Update paths in /home/mernst/.local/state/syncthing/config.xml (found via `syncthing -paths`).

# Remove default Syncthing folder:
rm -rf ~/Sync

===========================================================================

To change the name of a folder, it may be easiest to do this simultaneously on all machines:
 * shut down syncthing:  killall syncthing
 * rename the folder locally
 * edit ~/.config/syncthing/config.xml to rename
 * restart syncthing:  nohup synching &
 * I may want to update a temp directory name in ~/bin/src/mdedots/share/mdevccommit

===========================================================================

CSE installation:

# Follow instructions at https://syncthing.net/downloads/
# Get version number from https://syncthing.net/downloads/
# Essentially:
cd ~/bin/install
VER=v1.27.7
wget https://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/releases/download/${VER}/syncthing-linux-amd64-${VER}.tar.gz
tar xvf syncthing-linux-amd64-${VER}.tar.gz
(cd ~/bin/Linux-x86_64 && rm -f syncthing && ln -s ../install/syncthing-linux-amd64-${VER}/syncthing .)

===========================================================================

Ubuntu:

The syncthing available in the regular Ubuntu repositories was too old to work (as of Sep 2020).
So, follow the CSE installation instructions.
Finally, add syncthing to the Ubuntu "startup" applications.

===========================================================================

I use syncthing for:
~/private
~/sync
~/public_html/tmpNNNNN
~/prof/consulting

===========================================================================

General setup:

cd ~/sync && ln -s ../.stignoreglobal .stignore
cd ~/private && ln -s ../.stignoreglobal .stignore

